<promed@promedmail.org>
[Details on the recent outbreak in Beining, Jinzhaou city, Liaoning
province, (map at
<http://www.fallingrain.com/world/CH/19/Beining.html>) involving the
destruction of more than 2.5 million chickens, are included in
China's follow-up report No.7 to the OIE, dated 10 Nov 2005. See at
<http://oie.int/downld/AVIAN%20INFLUENZA/China%20Follow-up%20report%20No7.pdf>.
According to the update, 198 million chickens have been vaccinated in
the said province in response to the outbreak. 3 vaccines have been
applied:
1. Inactivated mono H5N2 Vaccine;
2. lnactivated recombinant H5N1 vaccine;
3. Live recombinant avian pox virus vectored H5 vaccine.
The quantities of each vaccine were not specified. For details on
contemporary HPAI vaccines, see 20050307.0680. - Mod.AS]
